---
import Base from '../../../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="You're in. Here's your prep."
  description="Your spot in the Build Your Own AI Personal Assistant email course is saved. Do this ten-minute prep and Day 1 becomes a build day."
  noindex
>
  <section class="container course-thanks panel">
    <p class="eyebrow">You're in</p>
    <h1>Saved. Day 1 lands Monday morning.</h1>
    <p>
      One email a day for a week, each ending with your assistant doing something real.
      Do the prep below today and Day 1 is a build day, not a setup day.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="container course-prep">
    <p class="eyebrow">Day 0: ten minutes of prep</p>
    <h2>Three things before Monday.</h2>
    <ol class="course-prep-list">
      <li>
        <h3>Install the Claude desktop app</h3>
        <p>
          Download it at <a href="https://claude.ai/download" rel="noopener">claude.ai/download</a>
          and sign in on a paid plan. The course uses the Cowork tab, which handles the
          setup work for you.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <h3>Pick your Google account</h3>
        <p>
          Know which account holds the calendar and email you actually live in. You
          connect both on Day 1, and the same account for each keeps it simple.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <h3>Decide what it gets to see</h3>
        <p>
          Your assistant reads what you connect, and anything it reads goes to Anthropic
          to be processed. The working rule from the class: if you would not want it
          known, do not give it the information. Email stays draft-only. Claude does not
          send mail on your behalf, so you review every reply before it goes anywhere.
        </p>
      </li>
    </ol>
    <p class="course-prep-extra">
      iPhone optional: on Day 2 you can have the morning brief texted to you. Nothing to
      do yet.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="container course-headstart panel">
    <p class="eyebrow">Want a head start</p>
    <h2>The written walkthrough is already public.</h2>
    <p>
      The course walks you through it one day at a time with the exact prompts. If you
      would rather see the whole build now, it lives at
      <a href="/ai-assistant/cowork/">the Claude Cowork walkthrough</a>. Day 1 brings
      you right back to it.
    </p>
  </section>
</Base>

<style>
  .course-thanks {
    margin-top: 4rem;
    padding: 1.75rem;
  }

  .course-thanks h1 {
    font-size: clamp(1.9rem, 4.5vw, 2.6rem);
    margin: 0.4rem 0 0.8rem;
  }

  .course-thanks p {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    max-width: 38rem;
  }

  .course-prep {
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
  }

  .course-prep-list {
    list-style: none;
    counter-reset: prep;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 1.4rem 0 0;
    display: grid;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .course-prep-list li {
    counter-increment: prep;
    background: var(--color-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 1.1rem 1.3rem 1.1rem 3.4rem;
    position: relative;
  }

  .course-prep-list li::before {
    content: counter(prep);
    position: absolute;
    left: 1.1rem;
    top: 1.15rem;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 999px;
    width: 1.6rem;
    height: 1.6rem;
    display: grid;
    place-items: center;
  }

  .course-prep-list h3 {
    margin: 0 0 0.35rem;
    font-size: 1.02rem;
  }

  .course-prep-list p {
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    font-size: 0.97rem;
  }

  .course-prep-extra {
    margin-top: 1rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }

  .course-headstart {
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 4rem;
    padding: 1.75rem;
  }

  .course-headstart p {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    max-width: 38rem;
  }
</style>
